menu "Unit Test Framework"

config PCIE_TEST_DRIVER
	bool "PCIe Test Driver Framework"
	default n
	help
	  PCIe Test Driver Framework is a comprehensive Linux kernel module
	  and user-space utilities for testing PCIe devices.
	  
	  The framework provides tools for:
	  - BAR (Base Address Register) access
	  - Configuration space operations
	  - Interrupt handling
	  - DMA operations
	  - Device enumeration and testing
	  
	  This framework is useful for PCIe hardware testing, validation,
	  and development. Enable this to build the test driver module and
	  associated utilities.
	  
	  If unsure, say N.

config PCIE_TEST_DRIVER_DEBUG
	bool "Enable debug output in PCIe Test Driver"
	depends on PCIE_TEST_DRIVER
	default n
	help
	  Enable verbose debug logging in the PCIe test driver module.
	  This will output detailed information about device operations,
	  BAR accesses, and interrupts to the kernel log (dmesg).
	  
	  If unsure, say N.

config BUILD_PCIE_TEST_UTILITY
	bool "Build PCIe Test Utility"
	depends on PCIE_TEST_DRIVER
	default y
	help
	  Build the user-space command-line utility for testing PCIe devices.
	  This utility provides an interface to interact with the kernel module
	  without writing custom applications.
	  
	  If unsure, say Y.

config BUILD_PCIE_TEST_SCRIPTS
	bool "Build PCIe Test Scripts"
	depends on PCIE_TEST_DRIVER
	default y
	help
	  Build automated test scripts for validating the PCIe test driver
	  framework. These scripts provide:
	  - Automated module build and loading
	  - Basic functionality tests
	  - Status checking and reporting
	  - Checkpoint tracking and reporting
	  
	  If unsure, say Y.

endmenu
